\begin{rSection}{PROJECTS}
\vspace{-1.25em}
\item \textbf{Object Detection and Image Classification using Machine Learning Algorithms | Self Project}
\\
\textit{{Objective - Build a Machine Learning model for detecting instances of objects in images and videos } }
\begin{itemize}
\vspace{-0.5em}
\item   {Implemented Boosted Cascade and Haar Cascade classifiers to effectively allow the machine to identify real-life objects in videos and images.}
\vspace{-0.5em}
\item   {Effectuated Haar Cascade to train with numerous positive and negative images and train the classifier.}
\vspace{-0.5em}
\item   {Used Python libraries such as NumPy, OpenCV, matplotlib, and Scikit-Learn for loading and processing of data and data visualization as well as haar cascade XML file and PNG image for implementation.}
\end{itemize}
\\
\item \textbf{Twitter Hate speech recognition using NLTK | Self Project}
\\
\textit{{Objective - Build a Machine Learning model to detect offensive or hate speech words in Twitter posts} }
\begin{itemize}
\vspace{-0.5em}
\item Developed a machine learning model for detecting hate speech on Twitter using Python, NLTK library, and Scikit-learn.
\vspace{-0.5em}
\item Cleaned and preprocessed the Twitter data by removing URLs, user handles, hashtags, stopwords, and non-alphabetic characters.
\vspace{-0.5em}
\item Administered TfidfVectorizer  to convert the preprocessed  text into feature vectors and trained a Logistic Regression model on the feature vectors to classify tweets as either hate speech or non-hate speech and achieved an accuracy of 93.8\%
\end{itemize}

\item \textbf{Face Mask Recognition system using CNNs | Self Project}
\\
\textit{{Objective - Build a Machine Learning model to recognize whether a person in an image is wearing face mask or not} }
\begin{itemize}
\vspace{-0.5em}
\item Trained the model using a dataset of images of people with and without masks, which was obtained from Kaggle using the Kaggle API. The images were resized to 128x128 pixels and converted to numpy arrays.
\vspace{-0.5em}
\item Plotted the loss and accuracy values during training and validation using matplotlib. Also, tested the model on new images and made predictions by resizing the images, scaling them, reshaping them, and using the model's predict() method.
\end{itemize}
\end{rSection} 

